Package org.opengis.wrapper.netcdf

Class NetcdfIdentifiedObject

  • Object
    • NetcdfIdentifiedObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Identifier, IdentifiedObject, ReferenceIdentifier
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NetcdfAxis, NetcdfCRS, NetcdfEllipsoid, NetcdfParameter, NetcdfProjection
    public abstract class NetcdfIdentifiedObject
extends Object
implements IdentifiedObject, ReferenceIdentifier, Serializable
    An IdentifiedObject abstract base class backed by some netCDF object. All methods in this class delegate their work to the wrapped netCDF object. Consequently any change in the wrapped object is immediately reflected in this NetcdfIdentifiedObject instance. However users are encouraged to not change the wrapped object after construction, since GeoAPI referencing objects are expected to be immutable.

    This base class assumes that netCDF objects have a single name and no alias. This assumption allows us to implement directly the Identifier interface. The netCDF object name is returned by the getCode() method.

    Since:
    3.1

      • getScope

        public InternationalString getScope()
        Returns the description of domain of usage, or limitations of usage, for which this object is valid. The default implementation returns null in all cases, since netCDF objects don't specify their scope.

        Scope is a Datum, ReferenceSystem and CoordinateOperation property.

        Returns:
        the domain of usage, or null if none.

      • getAnchorPoint

        public InternationalString getAnchorPoint()
        Returns a description, possibly including coordinates of an identified point or points, of the relationship used to anchor the coordinate system to the Earth or alternate object. The default implementation returns null since this simple implementation does not define anchor point.

        Anchor point is a Datum property.

        Returns:
        a description of the anchor point, or null if none.

      • getRealizationEpoch

        public Date getRealizationEpoch()
        Returns The time after which this datum definition is valid. The default implementation returns null since this simple implementation does not define realization epoch.

        Anchor point is a Datum property.

        Returns:
        the datum realization epoch, or null if not available.
